types.name: Application
types.description:
Represents a registered application within the system, encapsulating all relevant details
that identify and describe the application.

fields.name: appName
fields.description: The human-readable name of the application.

fields.name: publicKey
fields.description:
A public key associated with the application, used for cryptographic operations such as
verifying the identity of the application.

fields.name: iconURL
fields.description:
The URL pointing to the icon graphic for the application. This URL should link to an image
that visually represents the application, aiding in its identification and branding.

fields.name: gandalfID
fields.description: A unique identifier assigned to the application upon registration.

fields.name: appRegistrar
fields.description: The address of the user who registered the application.

types.name: ID
types.description: The `ID` scalar type represents a unique identifier, often used to refetch an object or as key for a cache. The ID type appears in a JSON response as a String; however, it is not intended to be human-readable. When expected as an input type, any string (such as "4") or integer (such as 4) input value will be accepted as an ID.

fields.name: getActivity
fields.description:
Retrieves a paginated list of activities based on a given data key and source.

Returns: A response object containing a list of activities, along with pagination information.

args.name: dataKey
args.description: A unique key that is generated after a user has completed the data submission flow.

args.name: source
args.description: A unique key that is generated after a user has completed the data submission flow.

args.name: limit
args.description: The maximum number of activities to return in a single response.

args.name: page
args.description: The page number of the activity list to retrieve, allowing for pagination through large sets of data.

fields.name: lookupActivity
fields.description:
Looks up a specific activity by its unique identifier (ID) and a data key.

Returns: An Activity object containing detailed information about the requested activity.

args.name: dataKey
args.description: A unique key that is generated after a user has completed the data submission flow.

args.name: activityId
args.description: The unique identifier (UUID) of the activity to retrieve.

fields.name: getAppByPublicKey
fields.description:
Retrieves an application by its public key.

Returns: An Application object that includes detailed information about the requested application.

args.name: publicKey
args.description: The public key associated with the desired application.
